	<description>	
		William Chyr is an independent game developer and visual artist based in Chicago. His work spans a variety of media, including web, print, and installation.
	</description>
		
	<histories>
		<history>
			<!--<header>Early history</header>-->
			<text>
			<![CDATA[A recipient of the Midwestern Voices and Visions Award, 
			William Chyr is a past artist-in-residence of the Bemis Center for Contemporary Arts, the Swatch Art Peace Hotel, and the Lawrence Arts Center. 
			He has received commissions from Beck’s, AOL, the Wormfarm Institute, and the Interior Design Show. 
			His work has been featured in a number of publications and media outlets, including NPR, TIME, Elle, and the Toronto Star.  <br /><br />
			
			Some of his more notable past creations include <a href="http://youtu.be/j7Lje51Ntb0" target="_blank">a limited-edition art label for Beck’s Beer</a>, 
			a crowdsourced novel - <a href="http://www.thecollabowriters.com/" target="_blank">The Collabowriters</a>, 
			and <a href="http://jezebel.com/5856336/how-i-made-the-first-feminine-hygiene-ad-to-show-blood" target="_blank">a somewhat infamous print ad</a>.<br /><br />
			
			Chyr holds a B.A. degree in Physics and Economics from the University of Chicago. 
			<br /><br />
			
			He is currently working on <a href="http://www.manifoldgarden.com/" target="_blank"><b><i>Manifold Garden</i></b></a>, an exploration-puzzle game set in an Escher-esque world. ]]>
			</text>	
